begin_memory_text: We talked about our jobs and where we lived. We found out that we both live in a rural area and that we both work in tech. We also talked about COVID life.
middle_memory_text: We discussed more about the pandemic and how we've been affected. We discussed how our jobs have been handling WFH and when we think things will get better.
end_memory_text: We talked about his heart condition and how it was caught. He said that it's not treatable, except with diet and exercise. We also discussed his wife's job and how she has been doing WFH.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well. I have a lot to do, but I feel pretty motivated. I am most excited/nervous to see how my side hustles go and how much I am able to accomplish. If I meet my goals or get close to them, I will feel really good.
critical_positive: I think we both figured out that we have similar backgrounds and similar jobs. We talked about that and how the pandemic has affected both of us. I think this worked well because we found out that we share a few of the same struggles in terms of working from home.
critical_negative: I could have asked better, more varied questions. The conversation largely got stuck on work, when we could have talked about other things. When he first appeared, I was going to asked about the stuff animal behind him, but I ended up not doing that. I think I should have talked about other things, or tried to at least.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked about what we did for work.  It was slightly awkward but once we started talking about our jobs it lessened drastically
middle_memory_text: Middle of the conversation was more about our jobs and how the pandemic has effected them.  We talk in more detail about these types of things
end_memory_text: We talked about my health and how we were dealing with the pandemic.  I shared more about my family and how we were specifically dealing with things
rest_of_day_open: This week will be interesting.  My job is in transition as we have lost our boss and are starting the process of hiring a new one.  I have entered my name into that list of people for consideration, as well, I have applied for a higher tier position at work
critical_positive: Both of us were fairly open and friendly.  Neither one of us seemed put off by each other.  We were able to discuss things freely and warmly. Both of us were working from home and had similar experiences about working a job from home.  Neither one became distracted and gave each other our full attention
critical_negative: We both faltered a few times trying to think of something to say or ask.  It appeared that both of us were trying to be respectful and not pry to deep or ask anything that was too personal.  Both of us were polite to a fault, I suppose.  I could try to ask more questions next time
